assertion_line: 22
expression: "normalize_output(&output, temp_dir.path(), &date)"
---
$ govctl rfc --help
RFC operations

Usage: govctl rfc [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>

Commands:
  list       List RFCs [aliases: ls]
  get        Get RFC metadata or specific field
  show       Show rendered RFC content
  new        Create a new RFC
  edit       Canonical path-first edit entrypoint
  set        Set RFC field value
  add        Add value to RFC array field
  remove     Remove value from RFC array field
  bump       Bump RFC version
  finalize   Finalize RFC status (draft → normative or deprecated)
  advance    Advance RFC phase
  deprecate  Deprecate RFC
  supersede  Supersede RFC
  render     Render a single RFC to markdown
  help       Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
  -C, --config <CONFIG>  Path to govctl config (TOML)
      --dry-run          Dry run: preview changes without writing files
  -h, --help             Print help

COMMON WORKFLOW:
    1. `govctl rfc list` to discover RFCs
    2. `govctl rfc get <ID> ...` for metadata/fields
    3. `govctl rfc show <ID>` for rendered prose
    4. `govctl rfc edit <ID> ...` to update content
    5. `govctl rfc finalize/advance/...` for lifecycle

START HERE:
    - New RFC: `govctl rfc new "Title"`
    - Inspect one RFC: `govctl rfc get RFC-0001`
    - Render one RFC: `govctl rfc show RFC-0001`
exit: 0
